'''List of Kofun in the Japanese Archipelago with the Name "Hyō"''' (「瓢」の付く日本列島の古墳一覧)
This article provides a list of kofun (ancient burial mounds) and kofun clusters in the **Japanese Archipelago** whose names include **"Hyō"** (瓢 / ひさご), which refers to a **gourd**.
== Overview == Throughout **Japan**, there are many kofun with names like **"Hyōtan-zuka"** (瓢箪塚 / ひょうたんづか, ひさごづか) and **"Hyōtan-yama"** (瓢箪山 / ひょうたんやま, ひさごやま). In addition, there are variations such as **"Hyō-zuka"** (瓢塚 / ひょうづか, ひさごづか), **"Hisago-zuka"**, and **"Hisago-yama"**, as well as names where **"Hyō"** is written in **hiragana**. These names are believed to originate from the resemblance of **keyhole-shaped kofun** (**zenpō-kōen-fun**) or **square-fronted kofun** (**zenpō-kōhō-fun**) to a **gourd (瓢箪, hisago / hyōtan)** when viewed from the side.
== Hyōtan-yama Kofun == {{main|Hyōtan-yama Kofun}} * **Komaka Hyōtan-yama Kofun** (駒岡瓢箪山古墳) - Located in **Tsurumi Ward, Yokohama City, Kanagawa Prefecture**, part of the **Komaka Kofun Cluster**. * **Hyōtan-yama Kofun (Kannami Town)** (瓢箪山古墳（函南町）) - Located in **Kannami Town, Tagata District, Shizuoka Prefecture**. * **Moriyama Hyōtan-yama Kofun** (守山瓢箪山古墳) - Located in **Moriyama Ward, Nagoya City, Aichi Prefecture**. * **Azuchi Hyōtan-yama Kofun** (安土瓢箪山古墳) - Located in **Ōmihachiman City, Shiga Prefecture**. * **Hyōtan-yama Kofun (Higashi-Osaka City)** (瓢箪山古墳（東大阪市）) - Located in **Higashi-Osaka City, Osaka Prefecture**, part of the **Yamahata Kofun Cluster**. * **Saki Hyōtan-yama Kofun** (佐紀瓢箪山古墳) - Located in **Nara City, Nara Prefecture**, part of the **Saki Tatenami Kofun Cluster**.
== Hyōtan-zuka Kofun == {{main|Hyōtan-zuka Kofun}} * **Hyōtan-zuka Kofun (Mooka City)** (瓢箪塚古墳（真岡市）) - Located in **Mooka City, Tochigi Prefecture**. * **Komori Hyōtan-zuka Kofun** (小森瓢箪塚古墳) - Located in **Shiroi City, Chiba Prefecture**{{sfn|Takahana|2005}}. * **Yamasaki Hyōtan-zuka Kofun** (山崎ひょうたん塚古墳) - Located in **Sakura City, Chiba Prefecture**. * **Hyōtan-zuka Kofun (Ebina City)** (瓢箪塚古墳（海老名市）) - Located in **Ebina City, Kanagawa Prefecture**, part of the **Kamihamada Kofun Cluster**. * **Hyōtan-zuka (Kobirasawa Kofun)** (ひょうたん塚) - Located in **Kōfu City, Yamanashi Prefecture**, an alternate name for **Kobirasawa Kofun** (小平沢古墳). * **Hyōtan-zuka Kofun (Shizuoka City)** (瓢箪塚古墳（静岡市）) - Located in **Shimizu Ward, Shizuoka City, Shizuoka Prefecture**, part of the **Nishinohara Kofun Cluster**.
== Other Kofun == {{main|Hyōzuka Kofun}} * **Hyōzuka Kofun (Kakegawa City)** (瓢塚古墳（掛川市）) - Located in **Kakegawa City, Shizuoka Prefecture**. * **Shiramizu Hyōzuka Kofun** (白水瓢塚古墳) - Located in **Kobe City, Hyogo Prefecture**. * **Yoro Hyōzuka Kofun** (丁瓢塚古墳) - Located in **Himeji City, Hyogo Prefecture**, part of the **Yoro Kofun Cluster**. * **Hisago-yama Kofun** (瓢山古墳) - Located in **Shōbara City, Hiroshima Prefecture**. * **Hisago-zuka Kofun (Kannonji City)** (ひさご塚古墳（観音寺市）) - Located in **Kannonji City, Kagawa Prefecture**. * **Hyōzuka Kofun (Karatsu City)** (瓢塚古墳（唐津市）) - Located in **Karatsu City, Saga Prefecture**. * **Hisago-zuka Kofun** (ひさご塚古墳) - Located in **Higashisonogi Town, Higashisonogi District, Nagasaki Prefecture**.
== References == {{Reflist}}
== Bibliography == *{{Cite book|lang=ja|first=Hiroyuki|last=Takahana|title=Chiba Prefecture Shiroi City Archaeological Investigation Report (Komori Hyōtan-zuka Kofun)|year=2005|date=2005-03-24|url=https://sitereports.nabunken.go.jp/ja/57027|series=Shiroi City Cultural Property Basic Investigation Report 4|publisher=Shiroi City Board of Education|ref=harv}}
