'''List of Kofun in the Japanese Archipelago with the Name "Hyō"''' (「瓢」の付く日本列島の古墳一覧)
This article provides a list of kofun (ancient Kofuns) and kofun clusters in the '''Japanese Archipelago''' whose names include '''"Hyō"''' (瓢 / ひさご), which refers to a '''gourd'''.
== Overview == Throughout '''Japan''', there are many kofun with names like '''"Hyōtan-zuka"''' (瓢箪塚 / ひょうたんづか, ひさごづか) and '''"Hyōtan-yama"''' (瓢箪山 / ひょうたんやま, ひさごやま). In addition, there are variations such as '''"Hyō-zuka"''' (瓢塚 / ひょうづか, ひさごづか), '''"Hisago-zuka"''', and '''"Hisago-yama"''', as well as names where '''"Hyō"''' is written in '''hiragana'''. These names are believed to originate from the resemblance of '''keyhole-shaped kofun''' ('''zenpō-kōen-fun''') or '''square-fronted kofun''' ('''zenpō-kōhō-fun''') to a '''gourd (瓢箪, hisago / hyōtan)''' when viewed from the side.
== {{ill|Hyōtan-yama Kofun|ja|瓢箪山古墳|12=draft}} == * {{ill|Komaka Hyōtan-yama Kofun|ja|駒岡瓢箪山古墳|12=draft}} - Located in '''Tsurumi Ward, Yokohama City, Kanagawa Prefecture''', part of the '''Komaka Kofun Cluster'''. * {{ill|Hyōtan-yama Kofun (Kannami Town)|ja|瓢箪山古墳 (函南町)|12=draft}} - Located in '''Kannami Town, Tagata District, Shizuoka Prefecture'''. * {{ill|Moriyama Hyōtan-yama Kofun|ja|守山瓢箪山古墳|12=draft}} - Located in '''Moriyama Ward, Nagoya City, Aichi Prefecture'''. * {{ill|Azuchi Hyōtan-yama Kofun|ja|安土瓢箪山古墳|12=draft}} - Located in '''Ōmihachiman City, Shiga Prefecture'''. * {{ill|Hyōtan-yama Kofun (Higashi-Osaka City)|ja|瓢箪山古墳 (東大阪市)|12=draft}} - Located in '''Higashi-Osaka City, Osaka Prefecture''', part of the '''Yamahata Kofun Cluster'''. * {{ill|Saki Hyōtan-yama Kofun|ja|佐紀瓢箪山古墳|12=draft}} - Located in '''Nara City, Nara Prefecture''', part of the '''Saki Tatenami Kofun Cluster'''.
== {{ill|Hyōtan-zuka Kofun|ja|瓢箪塚古墳|12=draft}} == * {{ill|Hyōtan-zuka Kofun (Mooka City)|ja|瓢箪塚古墳 (真岡市)|12=draft}} - Located in '''Mooka City, Tochigi Prefecture'''. * {{ill|Komori Hyōtan-zuka Kofun|ja|小森瓢箪塚古墳|12=draft}} - Located in '''Shiroi City, Chiba Prefecture'''{{sfn|Takahana|2005}}. * {{ill|Yamasaki Hyōtan-zuka Kofun|ja|山崎ひょうたん塚古墳|12=draft}} - Located in '''Sakura City, Chiba Prefecture'''. * {{ill|Hyōtan-zuka Kofun (Ebina City)|ja|瓢箪塚古墳 (海老名市)|12=draft}} - Located in '''Ebina City, Kanagawa Prefecture''', part of the '''Kamihamada Kofun Cluster'''. * {{ill|Hyōtan-zuka (Kobirasawa Kofun)|ja|小平沢古墳|12=draft}} - Located in '''Kōfu City, Yamanashi Prefecture''', an alternate name for '''Kobirasawa Kofun'''. * {{ill|Hyōtan-zuka Kofun (Shizuoka City)|ja|瓢箪塚古墳 (静岡市)|12=draft}} - Located in '''Shimizu Ward, Shizuoka City, Shizuoka Prefecture''', part of the '''Nishinohara Kofun Cluster'''.
== Other Kofun == * {{ill|Hyōzuka Kofun (Kakegawa City)|ja|瓢塚古墳 (掛川市)|12=draft}} - Located in '''Kakegawa City, Shizuoka Prefecture'''. * {{ill|Shiramizu Hyōzuka Kofun|ja|白水瓢塚古墳|12=draft}} - Located in '''Kobe City, Hyogo Prefecture'''. * {{ill|Yoro Hyōzuka Kofun|ja|丁瓢塚古墳|12=draft}} - Located in '''Himeji City, Hyogo Prefecture''', part of the '''Yoro Kofun Cluster'''. * {{ill|Hisago-yama Kofun|ja|瓢山古墳|12=draft}} - Located in '''Shōbara City, Hiroshima Prefecture'''. * {{ill|Hisago-zuka Kofun (Kannonji City)|ja|ひさご塚古墳 (観音寺市)|12=draft}} - Located in '''Kannonji City, Kagawa Prefecture'''. * {{ill|Hyōzuka Kofun (Karatsu City)|ja|瓢塚古墳 (唐津市)|12=draft}} - Located in '''Karatsu City, Saga Prefecture'''. * {{ill|Hisago-zuka Kofun|ja|ひさご塚古墳|12=draft}} - Located in '''Higashisonogi Town, Higashisonogi District, Nagasaki Prefecture'''.
